## Pull request overview

This PR advances the repo’s open-core architecture by decoupling premium blocks from the public core, introducing runtime mechanisms to (a) gate premium *core* features via licensing and (b) make premium *blocks* optional without causing build-time import failures.

**Changes:**
- Introduces a core block registry (`blockRegistry`) and license feature gating (`licenseValidator`), and re-exports them via `core/index.ts`.
- Updates AI/Data/Marketplace API routes and dashboard pages to gracefully handle missing premium blocks (return 404 / redirect).
- Stages premium block source under `proprietary/`, updates Drizzle schema discovery, and documents the new model (manifest + README/CLAUDE + plan).

